## 2. Product Requirements Document (PRD)

### 2.1 Problem Statement

**Current State:**
- 12+ AI agent modules across 5 ads-related apps operate in complete isolation
- No agent can discover what other agents are running or their current status
- Cross-agent coordination requires human relay via Slack (hours of latency)
- When Agent A discovers information Agent B needs, there is no delivery mechanism
- Complex multi-step ad workflows (creative → scoring → launch → monitor → optimize) run as disconnected serial steps
- No structured escalation — agents dump everything into Slack at equal priority

**Desired State:**
- Any agent can discover all other active agents and their current tasks
- Agents can send fire-and-forget notifications to other agents
- Agents can ask blocking questions to other agents and receive answers in real-time
- Complex ad workflows self-orchestrate across agents without human relay
- Structured 3-tier escalation (BLOCKING/INTERVIEW/UPDATE) to human supervisors
- Full audit trail of all inter-agent communication in Supabase

### 2.2 User Stories

1. **As the Creative Scoring Agent**, when I detect a creative with fatigueScore > 80, I want to SEND a notification to Campaign Ops Agent so it can pause the associated ad set automatically.

2. **As the DTC Strategy Agent**, when I detect a growth stage transition (e.g., Stage 1 → Stage 2), I want to ASK the Budget Optimizer Agent "What is the current daily spend and recommended new allocation?" and receive a structured answer before generating the new strategy.

3. **As the Campaign Ops Agent**, when I'm about to launch a campaign but the creative hasn't been scored yet, I want to ASK the Creative Scoring Agent to score the creative and block until I receive the quality score.

4. **As the UMDM ETL Agent**, when I detect a governance violation (naming convention breach), I want to SEND an alert to the Campaign Ops Agent with the violation details so it can auto-fix or flag.

5. **As the Offer Engine Agent**, when building a new offer funnel, I want to ASK the Revenue Intelligence Agent "What is the current AOV and LTV for this product category?" and use the response to set pricing.

6. **As any agent**, when I hit an ambiguity that requires human judgment, I want to ESCALATE with the appropriate tier (BLOCKING for immediate decisions, INTERVIEW for multi-question sessions, UPDATE for FYI progress reports).

7. **As Rashida (human supervisor)**, I want to see a real-time dashboard of all active agent sessions, pending asks, and escalations so I can intervene when needed.

### 2.3 Success Metrics

| Metric | Target | Measurement |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| Agent-to-agent message delivery time | < 2 seconds | Timestamp delta (sent → received) |
| Blocking ask/reply round-trip | < 30 seconds (avg) | Timestamp delta (ask sent → reply received) |
| Human relay elimination | > 80% of cross-agent coordination automated | Before/after comparison |
| Escalation response time | < 5 min for BLOCKING tier | Slack timestamp delta |
| Message delivery reliability | > 99.5% | Delivered / sent ratio |
| Agent discovery accuracy | 100% of active agents visible | Session registry vs actual |
| Audit trail completeness | 100% messages logged | Supabase row count validation |

### 2.4 Non-Functional Requirements

- **Latency:** Message delivery < 2s via Supabase Realtime; polling fallback < 5s
- **Availability:** Inherits Supabase uptime (99.9%+)
- **Scalability:** Support 50+ concurrent agent sessions
- **Persistence:** All messages stored permanently in Supabase (queryable, auditable)
- **Security:** RLS policies — agents can only read messages addressed to them
- **Observability:** Every message logged with sender, receiver, type, timestamp, payload size
- **Backward Compatibility:** Existing Convex-based apps unchanged — AIP is additive

### 2.5 Out of Scope (Phase 2+)

- Video/audio streaming between agents
- Cross-workspace agent communication (different Supabase instances)
- Agent-to-agent file transfer (use existing Supabase Storage)
- Machine learning on communication patterns
- Natural language agent-to-agent dialogue (structured messages only)

