### 3.2 Agent Registration Flow

```
Agent starts up
    │
    ▼
Register with AIP
    │  INSERT into agent_intercom_sessions:
    │  {agent_id, agent_name, app_source, capabilities[], status: "idle", heartbeat_at}
    │
    ▼
Start heartbeat loop (every 30 seconds)
    │  UPDATE agent_intercom_sessions SET heartbeat_at = NOW(), status = current_status
    │
    ▼
Subscribe to Supabase Realtime
    │  Channel: "agent-intercom"
    │  Filter: postgres_changes on agent_intercom_messages WHERE receiver_id = my_agent_id
    │
    ▼
Agent is now discoverable and can send/receive messages
    │
    ▼
On shutdown: UPDATE status = "offline", unsubscribe from Realtime
```

### 3.3 Message Flow — SEND (Fire-and-Forget)

```
Agent A wants to notify Agent B:
    │
    ▼
Agent A checks session registry:
    │  SELECT * FROM agent_intercom_sessions WHERE agent_name = 'campaign-ops'
    │
    ├── Agent B not found → log warning, skip
    │
    ▼
Agent A inserts message:
    │  INSERT INTO agent_intercom_messages {
    │    sender_id, receiver_id, type: "send",
    │    payload: {text, data, attachments},
    │    status: "sent", expects_reply: false
    │  }
    │
    ▼
Supabase Realtime triggers notification to Agent B
    │
    ▼
Agent B receives message → processes inline → optionally acts
    │
    ▼
Agent B updates message status:
    │  UPDATE agent_intercom_messages SET status = "delivered", delivered_at = NOW()
    │
    ▼
Done (Agent A never blocked)
```

### 3.4 Message Flow — ASK (Blocking)

```
Agent A needs an answer from Agent B:
    │
    ▼
Agent A inserts ASK message:
    │  INSERT INTO agent_intercom_messages {
    │    sender_id, receiver_id, type: "ask",
    │    payload: {question, context, required_fields},
    │    status: "pending", expects_reply: true
    │  }
    │
    ▼
Agent A enters WAIT state:
    │  Subscribe to postgres_changes on agent_intercom_messages
    │  WHERE reply_to_message_id = this_message_id AND type = "reply"
    │  Polling fallback: SELECT every 3 seconds
    │  Timeout: 10 minutes (configurable per-agent)
    │
    ▼
Supabase Realtime notifies Agent B of incoming ASK
    │
    ▼
Agent B processes the question:
    │  - Reads payload.question and payload.context
    │  - Computes/looks up the answer
    │  - Formats structured response
    │
    ▼
Agent B inserts REPLY:
    │  INSERT INTO agent_intercom_messages {
    │    sender_id: B, receiver_id: A, type: "reply",
    │    reply_to_message_id: original_ask_id,
    │    payload: {answer, data},
    │    status: "sent"
    │  }
    │
    ▼
Agent A's subscription fires → receives reply
    │
    ▼
Agent A continues execution with the answer in context
    │  (zero context loss — same execution context)
    │
    ▼
Both messages updated: status = "completed"
```

### 3.5 Escalation Flow — Human-in-the-Loop

```
Agent hits ambiguity requiring human judgment:
    │
    ├── Tier 1: BLOCKING (needs immediate decision)
    │   │  INSERT INTO agent_intercom_escalations {
    │   │    agent_id, tier: "blocking", question, context,
    │   │    timeout_minutes: 10, status: "pending"
    │   │  }
    │   │  → Slack message to #v-infra with ⚠️ priority
    │   │  → Agent blocks until human replies or timeout
    │   ▼
    │   Human replies in Slack → webhook → INSERT reply → agent unblocks
    │
    ├── Tier 2: INTERVIEW (needs multiple structured answers)
    │   │  INSERT INTO agent_intercom_escalations {
    │   │    agent_id, tier: "interview",
    │   │    questions: [{id, question, type, options}],
    │   │    timeout_minutes: 30, status: "pending"
    │   │  }
    │   │  → Slack message with structured form
    │   │  → Agent blocks until all answers received
    │   ▼
    │   Human answers all questions → agent unblocks with structured data
    │
    └── Tier 3: UPDATE (fire-and-forget progress)
        │  INSERT INTO agent_intercom_escalations {
        │    agent_id, tier: "update", message, data,
        │    status: "sent"
        │  }
        │  → Slack message to thread (informational)
        ▼
        Agent continues immediately (no blocking)
```

### 3.6 Agent Capability Registry

Each agent registers its capabilities so other agents can discover *what* to ask *whom*:

| Agent Name | App Source | Capabilities | Can Answer |
|------------|-----------|-------------|------------|
| `creative-factory` | Ad Campaign Engine | `generate_creative`, `score_creative`, `batch_variants` | Creative quality scores, hook analysis, visual recommendations |
| `creative-scorer` | Ad Campaign Engine | `score_creative`, `fatigue_detection` | Quality scores (0-100), fatigue alerts, launch/optimize/rework verdicts |
| `campaign-ops` | Ad Campaign Engine | `launch_campaign`, `pause_campaign`, `adjust_budget` | Campaign status, budget data, performance metrics |
| `budget-optimizer` | Ad Campaign Engine | `optimize_budget`, `reallocate` | Current spend, recommended allocation, scaling signals |
| `audience-builder` | Ad Campaign Engine | `build_audience`, `rfm_segment` | Audience sizes, segment data, lookalike recommendations |
| `dtc-strategist` | Ad Campaign Engine | `detect_stage`, `generate_strategy` | Growth stage, strategic recommendations, KPI targets |
| `copy-engine` | Ad Campaign Engine | `generate_copy`, `headline_matrix` | Ad copy variants, headlines, hooks, frameworks |
| `offer-architect` | Offer Engine v3 | `build_offer`, `price_offer`, `ab_test` | Offer structures, pricing, conversion predictions |
| `revenue-intel` | Revenue Intel Engine | `deal_analysis`, `forecast`, `enrichment` | AOV, LTV, deal scores, revenue projections |
| `umdm-etl` | UMDM | `sync_data`, `governance_check`, `anomaly_detect` | Cross-channel metrics, governance violations, anomalies |
| `cro-agent` | Clarity CRO | `score_page`, `heatmap_analysis` | CRO scores, objection patterns, conversion blockers |
| `tracking-intel` | Ad Campaign Engine | `pixel_audit`, `capi_check` | Tracking health, pixel status, event coverage |

### 3.7 Pre-Built Coordination Workflows

#### Workflow 1: Creative → Score → Launch Pipeline

```
creative-factory generates batch of 20 creatives
    │
    ▼
creative-factory SENDS to creative-scorer:
    "Score these 20 creatives: [creative_ids]"
    │
    ▼
creative-scorer processes all 20, SENDS results back:
    {scored: [{id, score, verdict}...], launch_ready: [ids], rework: [ids]}
    │
    ▼
creative-factory ASKS campaign-ops:
    "Launch these 8 approved creatives into campaign X. Confirm launch."
    │  (blocks until campaign-ops confirms)
    │
    ▼
campaign-ops launches, REPLIES:
    {launched: true, campaign_id: "xxx", ad_set_ids: [...]}
    │
    ▼
creative-factory logs results, notifies human via UPDATE escalation
```

#### Workflow 2: Fatigue Detection → Auto-Pause → Refresh

```
creative-scorer detects fatigue (score > 80) on creative C-123
    │
    ▼
creative-scorer SENDS to campaign-ops:
    {action: "pause_creative", creative_id: "C-123", reason: "fatigue_score_85"}
    │
    ▼
campaign-ops pauses the ad set, SENDS to creative-factory:
    {action: "generate_replacement", original_id: "C-123", campaign_id: "X"}
    │
    ▼
creative-factory generates replacement, SENDS to creative-scorer for scoring
    │
    ▼
(Pipeline continues from Workflow 1)
```

#### Workflow 3: Growth Stage Transition → Full Re-Strategy

```
dtc-strategist detects Stage 1 → Stage 2 transition
    │
    ▼
dtc-strategist ASKS budget-optimizer:
    "Current daily spend and recommended Stage 2 allocation?"
    │  (blocks)
    │
    ▼
budget-optimizer REPLIES:
    {current_daily: 150, recommended: {meta: 200, google: 100}, scaling_signal: "vertical"}
    │
    ▼
dtc-strategist ASKS audience-builder:
    "Current top-performing audiences and recommended Stage 2 expansion?"
    │  (blocks)
    │
    ▼
audience-builder REPLIES:
    {top_audiences: [...], expansion: [{type: "lookalike", seed: "...", size: "3%"}]}
    │
    ▼
dtc-strategist generates full Stage 2 strategy document
    │
    ▼
dtc-strategist ESCALATES (INTERVIEW tier) to human:
    "Stage transition detected. Approve new strategy? [Yes/No/Modify]"
    Questions: [{budget_approval}, {audience_approval}, {timeline}]
```

#### Workflow 4: Cross-App Offer Pricing

```
offer-architect building new upsell for FGS
    │
    ▼
offer-architect ASKS revenue-intel:
    "What is current AOV, LTV, and second-purchase rate for 'personalized gifts' category?"
    │  (blocks)
    │
    ▼
revenue-intel REPLIES:
    {aov: 42.50, ltv: 127.80, second_purchase_rate: 0.31, avg_days_to_second: 45}
    │
    ▼
offer-architect ASKS umdm-etl:
    "What is blended ROAS and CPA for Meta campaigns targeting gift buyers?"
    │  (blocks)
    │
    ▼
umdm-etl REPLIES:
    {blended_roas: 3.2, meta_cpa: 18.50, google_cpa: 22.10}
    │
    ▼
offer-architect calculates optimal upsell price using LTV and CPA data
    │
    ▼
offer-architect SENDS to cro-agent:
    "Score this offer page for conversion optimization: [page_url]"
```

